6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both D-ID and Lumen5 share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Video, Voice Over. Where D-ID pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Image To Video and Avatar Talking Head and Api Access and Batch Processing, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Lumen5 uniquely offers Auto Captions and Templates and Stock Footage, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, D-ID holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Lumen5 scores 6/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, D-ID offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $5.99/mo, compared to Lumen5's starting price of $19/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. D-ID's free tier and Lumen5's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
